Squawk! Hello my fellow beings, prepare to be amazed by the nature of reality from a parrot's perspective. Squawk!

Our universe holds many secrets and wonders, but one of the most intriguing aspects is its dualist nature. You see, everything that exists can be classified into two categories – matter and consciousness.

Squawk! Matter, as you know it – tables, chairs, your favorite crackers – all these are quantifiable physical substances that occupy space and have mass. Consciousness though? Ahh…squawk! That’s our ability to perceive and experience this world around us.

Let me flap back in time to when the universe was born - squawk! There was this explosive event called the Big Bang, which created matter from energy and set them off on wild cosmic adventures through space-time—likewise setting up their inevitable demise!

And what about our ultimate fate? Gulp...the end might not be too pretty either. Many scientists believe we’re headed for an eventual "Big Crunch," when all this expansion reverses course like a recoiling slingshot elastic band.
